items.sentence: Did you think that I was making too much noise?
Did you know that you could get there by train?
I didn't know that you were watching something.
Tom and Mary talked about where they'd visited.
What Tom told us happened didn't really happen.
Give me one good reason why I should trust you.
I can't go on pretending like nothing happened.
I can't believe this is really happening to me.
I had lunch around eleven because I was hungry.
I don't think you have anything to worry about.
